1
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:08,400
My boss is here, over there.

2
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:10,680
I missed you so much.

3
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:17,240
I won't hide or lie to Pun anymore.
Whatever happens, happens.

4
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:18,600
- Pie, but I think--
- Mom!

5
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:19,800
I've made my decision.

6
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:22,000
I'm ready to face the truth,
no matter what.

7
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:24,600
If they're not real, not genuine,

8
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:28,400
they'll eventually fall apart
and reveal their true nature.

9
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:29,760
What on earth are you doing?

10
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:31,640
You're so embarrassing.

11
00:02:31,720 --> 00:02:34,720
<i>If you want to leave, I can help.</i>

12
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:41,600
<i>He might be a better match</i>
<i>for her than for me.</i>

13
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:43,800
<i>At this point, if Pun really chooses Mink,</i>

14
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:45,840
<i>I'll accept it.</i>

15
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:52,360
Thanks a lot
for looking after Pie yesterday.

16
00:02:52,440 --> 00:02:54,280
No problem. It was nothing.

17
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:57,680
How did yesterday's work go?
Was everything okay?

18
00:02:58,720 --> 00:02:59,680
It was fine.

19
00:02:59,760 --> 00:03:02,240
A bit unfamiliar, though.

20
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:08,160
I saw Mink's post. You looked good in it.

21
00:03:10,160 --> 00:03:11,480
The team is professional.

22
00:03:13,920 --> 00:03:14,800
Hey.

23
00:03:17,320 --> 00:03:20,600
Do you know that Mink likes you?

24
00:03:21,880 --> 00:03:22,880
I know.

25
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:30,280
So, don't you think that post
was a bit much?

26
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,880
I feel like it's a bit over the top.

27
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:35,120
Are you jealous?

28
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:36,400
No.

29
00:03:36,920 --> 00:03:38,680
You're married,
and now another woman is involved.

30
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:40,120
I'm concerned.

31
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:44,160
And besides, Mink is being
way too obvious about it.

32
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,120
Win.

33
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:48,080
It doesn't matter what she thinks.

34
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:50,440
What matters is what I think.

35
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:52,840
Don't worry about me.

36
00:03:52,920 --> 00:03:54,760
I know exactly how to handle things.

37
00:03:58,760 --> 00:04:00,120
And this afternoon,

38
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:02,560
Mink's scheduled a work update meeting.

39
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:04,280
Stop worrying about me.

40
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:07,480
Focus on yourself.
You've got to present the work to her.

41
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:15,360
Did you see the feedback?

42
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:18,000
Lots of comments from netizens
thinking Pun and I are a couple.

43
00:04:18,079 --> 00:04:19,320
Funny, right?

44
00:04:19,399 --> 00:04:21,880
It's funny, yeah.
His real wife is sitting over there.

45
00:04:21,959 --> 00:04:23,520
What do the netizens know?

46
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:25,920
They are commenting
based on how they feel.

47
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:29,200
They think Pun and I make a good match,
so they're commenting like that.

48
00:04:29,720 --> 00:04:32,240
Time's up for chatting. It's meeting time.

49
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:36,600
Don't forget to separate work
from personal stuff, Mink.

50
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:39,080
Whatever you do, respect the friendship

51
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:42,000
and the fact
that he's your friend's partner. Got it?

52
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:44,440
Go to the meeting now.

53
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:48,800
This is the house plan I designed
to turn it into a fabric museum.

54
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:52,840
I've made changes
from the original design I showed you.

55
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:57,720
Inside, I've restructured some rooms
and expanded others

56
00:04:57,800 --> 00:05:01,080
to showcase the standout fabrics
so visitors can see them clearly,

57
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:03,480
just as you and Mr. Dech requested.

58
00:05:04,280 --> 00:05:07,600
It's way better than I expected.
Uncle will love it.

59
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:09,480
Thank you.

60
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:15,240
Alright, let's move on
and look at the museum content.

61
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:22,080
For this fabric museum,

62
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:24,440
we plan to make it a historical house.

63
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:27,920
We'll tell the story of history
through ancient fabrics,

64
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:31,360
starting from Mr. Dech's ancestors
who collected fabrics

65
00:05:31,440 --> 00:05:34,160
and continuing up to the present.

66
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:36,880
Right now, we're rushing
to catalog the ancient fabrics

67
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:40,720
and gather information
to create interesting content.

68
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:42,960
So, it's not finished yet?

69
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:58,800
It's normal for it not to be finished yet.

70
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:02,680
With so many fabrics to display,

71
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:05,200
the research takes time.

72
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:06,960
Win's right.

73
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:08,680
Your family has hundreds of fabrics,

74
00:06:08,760 --> 00:06:11,280
and each one
has a serious history behind it.

75
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:13,920
Mink.

76
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:17,080
A good project takes time,

77
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:19,920
to ensure the information
is accurate and detailed.

78
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:32,560
If you confirm that,
then I'm okay with it.

79
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:37,840
So, the house design is approved.

80
00:06:37,920 --> 00:06:39,960
I'll talk to Uncle about it.

81
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:41,560
As for the fabric content,

82
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:46,240
even if it's slow, if Pun says to wait…

83
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:50,400
I'll wait as he says.

84
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:06,160
I'll leave now.

85
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,760
Pun, can you walk me to the car?

86
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:12,320
Uncle has something for you,
so you can pick it up too.

87
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,880
I'm going to my car to grab something.

88
00:07:25,960 --> 00:07:28,120
I'll get it for you. Go ahead.

89
00:07:31,840 --> 00:07:32,840
Thanks a lot, Win.

90
00:07:33,440 --> 00:07:34,600
Mink.

91
00:07:35,320 --> 00:07:37,440
Just give it to Win.
I'll get back to work.

92
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:39,480
Go on.

93
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:41,120
Go ahead.

94
00:08:03,760 --> 00:08:05,800
Are you doing this for Pun or for Pie?

95
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:09,640
It's for both of them. They're family.

96
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:13,880
But you don't look at Pie
the way you look at your brother's wife.

97
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:17,440
What are you trying to stir up with me?

98
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:21,320
Have you asked yourself
how you look at someone else's husband?

99
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:25,200
I'm here to work.

100
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:27,560
Don't drag me into your drama.

101
00:08:28,080 --> 00:08:29,200
Got it?

102
00:08:32,640 --> 00:08:36,159
As for the gift you mentioned,
I'm guessing it's just a lie.

103
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:37,480
There's probably nothing.

104
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:39,039
I'm going back to work now.

105
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:55,160
Thanks a lot, Bee.

106
00:08:58,600 --> 00:08:59,840
Pie.

107
00:08:59,920 --> 00:09:01,480
I've got an appointment with Dr. Bee.

108
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:04,520
We'll discuss the IVF process tomorrow.

109
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:06,240
I've had Rok clear my schedule already.

110
00:09:12,880 --> 00:09:13,880
Okay.

111
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:22,240
But this time,

112
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,360
you really need
to take care of your diet, alright?

113
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:28,040
You need to avoid spicy food.

114
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:32,040
No raw food and anything that isn't clean.

115
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:37,000
Got it.

116
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:39,440
Pun, don't worry.

117
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:42,240
I'll take good care of myself.

118
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:45,240
I'll be ready to talk
to the doctor properly.

119
00:09:58,240 --> 00:10:00,280
No way, Pie!

120
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:02,200
You can't let Pun find out about this.

121
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:04,760
Look, Pie.

122
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:07,000
I won't let him find out about…

123
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:11,160
the time you were pregnant
and had a miscarriage.

124
00:10:11,840 --> 00:10:15,080
Pun's mom already has an issue
with us as it is.

125
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:17,920
And if Pun finds out,
his mom will know too.

126
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:21,040
Oh, this will turn into a huge deal, Pie.

127
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:23,960
Mom, if it happens, it happens.
I'm ready for the drama.

128
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:25,320
But I'm not ready.

129
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:27,440
If you're not ready,
then you have to get ready.

130
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:30,280
The truth is the truth, Mom.

131
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:33,920
Even if we run from it our whole lives,
it will catch up one day.

132
00:10:35,920 --> 00:10:36,760
Mom.

133
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:39,600
Pun has an appointment
with his doctor friend tomorrow.

134
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:42,560
And I'm not going to get drained
from taking laxatives again.

135
00:10:42,640 --> 00:10:43,640
- I'm not doing that.
- I know!

136
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:44,880
I won't use it anymore.

137
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:48,440
If we do the same thing again,
Pun will figure it out.

138
00:10:58,360 --> 00:10:59,360
Pie.

139
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:01,680
Don't worry.

140
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:04,920
I'll handle tomorrow's situation.

141
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:07,760
What are you going to do, Mom?

142
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:29,360
Pun, over here.

143
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:35,400
What's going on, Mom?

144
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:38,000
Why is it so important
that you couldn't talk on the phone?

145
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:41,200
It's really important. So important that…

146
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:44,680
I actually thought for a long time
about whether I should tell you.

147
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:47,480
If it's that important,
then you should tell me.

148
00:11:47,560 --> 00:11:51,920
But if I tell you,
you need to stay calm and composed, okay?

149
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:54,160
Okay.

150
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:56,280
I'll listen carefully and stay calm.

151
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:58,640
So here's the thing.

152
00:11:58,720 --> 00:12:02,040
I happened to be in Ratchaburi
for some business.

153
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,160
And I accidentally discovered
something that…

154
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:06,280
really shocked me.

155
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:10,320
I've been thinking ever since
about whether I should tell you and how.

156
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:11,200
Just tell me.

157
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:13,880
I'm waiting to hear it.

158
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:20,920
If I just tell you,
you might not believe me.

159
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,040
So, let's do this.

160
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:25,400
Just look at the photos yourself.

161
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:08,280
Where and when did you meet my dad?

162
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:10,040
A few days ago.

163
00:13:10,120 --> 00:13:12,480
And I think Mr. Sil
is probably still there,

164
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:15,520
because I heard from your family
that he went for a meditation retreat.

165
00:13:17,920 --> 00:13:19,080
Does Pie know about this?

166
00:13:19,160 --> 00:13:21,360
No one knows. I haven't told anyone.

167
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:23,040
You're the first one I'm telling.

168
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:25,360
I didn't reveal myself to Mr. Sil either.

169
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:32,400
I think just a photo
might not tell the whole truth.

170
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:35,120
I want you to see it for yourself.

171
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:36,200
Tomorrow.

172
00:13:39,880 --> 00:13:41,200
Tomorrow?

173
00:13:44,280 --> 00:13:47,680
- But…
- Pie said you have a doctor's appointment?

174
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,200
Yes.

175
00:13:52,640 --> 00:13:54,480
Then let her go alone.

176
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:56,920
The doctor's your friend, right?

177
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:59,560
Can you reschedule, saying it's urgent?

178
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:02,800
Then you and I can go together,
and you can see for yourself.

179
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:05,680
Hurry up before your dad
leaves that house,

180
00:14:05,760 --> 00:14:08,320
or you won't know the truth.

181
00:14:23,560 --> 00:14:26,960
The mistress is really something,
isn't she?

182
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:31,760
She knows the man is already married,
yet she still wants him.

183
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:33,400
What are you watching?

184
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:37,680
Just a pointless, cheesy soap opera
about husbands and wives.

185
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:40,800
Let's watch something more meaningful.

186
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:42,240
Hold on, ma'am.

187
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:46,080
Every time we put on a documentary,
you fall asleep.

188
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:48,920
Hey, are you mocking me?

189
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,320
No, not at all.

190
00:14:54,920 --> 00:14:57,480
Pun, come sit here.

191
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:01,640
Is there something
you want to talk to me about?

192
00:15:01,720 --> 00:15:03,920
And why are you coming here so late?

193
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:05,840
Wait.

194
00:15:06,640 --> 00:15:07,600
Did you argue with your wife?

195
00:15:08,760 --> 00:15:10,160
No, Mom.

196
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:13,200
I just stopped by to visit.

197
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:17,680
Where's Dad?

198
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:20,800
He went to a meditation retreat.

199
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:28,360
Does he go often?

200
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:34,560
He didn't use to,
but now he goes too often.

201
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:37,600
He just went last month,
and now he's gone again.

202
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:41,080
I don't know what kind
of peace he's looking for.

203
00:15:42,720 --> 00:15:44,240
Anyway, why are you asking?

204
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:47,680
Just curious, Mom.

205
00:15:49,040 --> 00:15:51,200
I've just noticed,

206
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:54,480
I haven't seen him
around the house lately.

207
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:57,080
You're not alone there.

208
00:15:57,160 --> 00:15:59,080
I haven't seen him much either.

209
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:00,840
He complains about being busy with work,

210
00:16:00,920 --> 00:16:03,480
but he's about to retire,
so I don't know why he's so busy.

211
00:16:03,560 --> 00:16:06,920
When he has free time,
he disappears for a meditation retreat.

212
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:08,840
He's hardly home.

213
00:16:11,280 --> 00:16:12,880
Look, Tian.

214
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:20,720
Let's see if the wife
can catch her husband in the act.

215
00:16:21,320 --> 00:16:23,600
The husband's been gone for days
with his mistress.

216
00:16:24,840 --> 00:16:27,600
Isn't that suspicious, ma'am?

217
00:16:27,680 --> 00:16:28,520
Yes.

218
00:16:29,160 --> 00:16:32,720
If she can't catch him,
then the female lead is just too dumb.

219
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:33,800
Exactly.

220
00:16:50,480 --> 00:16:52,560
PIE'S MOM

221
00:16:57,640 --> 00:16:58,920
I've made up my mind.

222
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:02,800
I'm going to see it for myself.

223
00:17:03,520 --> 00:17:04,720
I'll see you tomorrow.

224
00:17:06,760 --> 00:17:07,920
Mom.

225
00:17:08,440 --> 00:17:10,119
Please don't tell Pie about this.

226
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:13,280
I don't want her stressing
before the doctor.

227
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:37,480
You want me to go
to the doctor alone tomorrow?

228
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:39,240
Yes.

229
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:42,600
I've told my friend you'll go
for the check-up alone tomorrow.

230
00:17:42,680 --> 00:17:43,720
I'll go another day.

231
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:46,520
I have something important to do.

232
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:48,520
What is it?

233
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:50,800
I'll tell you once everything's settled.

234
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:17,720
Mom, why did Pun ask me
to go to the doctor alone?

235
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:18,960
What did you do?

236
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:21,240
I haven't done anything yet.

237
00:18:21,320 --> 00:18:25,160
Maybe it's fate,
keeping Pun busy with something important.

238
00:18:25,240 --> 00:18:26,800
<i>It's probably for the best.</i>

239
00:18:27,560 --> 00:18:29,040
Hey, Pie.

240
00:18:29,120 --> 00:18:33,200
Don't mention the miscarriage tomorrow
when you go alone.

241
00:18:33,720 --> 00:18:36,680
And if the doctor asks,
just lie about it, okay?

242
00:19:05,280 --> 00:19:09,160
Let's take my car,
so Mr. Sil won't recognize it.

243
00:19:13,560 --> 00:19:14,640
Shall we go now?

244
00:19:16,640 --> 00:19:17,520
Okay.

245
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:05,720
Does your mom
suspect anything about your dad?

246
00:20:07,320 --> 00:20:08,680
I don't want to talk about this yet.

247
00:20:12,520 --> 00:20:14,720
Let me see for myself
if my dad is really doing this.

248
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:18,560
Once you see for yourself,

249
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:21,160
make sure you spend more time
with your mom.

250
00:20:23,360 --> 00:20:25,320
I've been through this before.

251
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:30,000
I know how painful it is
to be betrayed by someone you love.

252
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:44,240
Ms. Phitpicha, please meet the doctor.

253
00:20:46,240 --> 00:20:47,120
Yes.

254
00:21:00,360 --> 00:21:01,480
You've been married for over two years.

255
00:21:01,560 --> 00:21:02,720
Have you used contraception?

256
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:05,360
No, we've been trying naturally
the whole time.

257
00:21:05,880 --> 00:21:09,000
If you've been trying naturally
for over a year with no success,

258
00:21:09,080 --> 00:21:10,840
it's considered infertility.

259
00:21:11,640 --> 00:21:13,480
It's good that you came to see me.

260
00:21:13,560 --> 00:21:16,400
But honestly,
you should have come with Pun.

261
00:21:16,480 --> 00:21:18,680
I've told him, but he didn't believe me.

262
00:21:18,760 --> 00:21:20,960
He wanted you to come first.

263
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:23,160
He's quite stubborn, huh?

264
00:21:23,240 --> 00:21:25,480
I'm speaking as a friend, not a doctor.

265
00:21:25,560 --> 00:21:26,440
Don't tell him I said that.

266
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:28,960
Yes.

267
00:21:29,040 --> 00:21:30,520
That's just how he is.

268
00:21:31,040 --> 00:21:33,880
Do you have any medical conditions?

269
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:35,520
No.

270
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:38,040
NO MEDICAL CONDITIONS

271
00:21:38,120 --> 00:21:39,480
Alright.

272
00:21:39,560 --> 00:21:42,200
Do you drink alcohol or smoke?

273
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:45,880
I drink occasionally at social events,
but I don't smoke.

274
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:48,520
Have you ever been pregnant
or had a miscarriage?

275
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:54,240
<i>Don't mention the miscarriage tomorrow.</i>

276
00:21:56,600 --> 00:21:57,760
No, never.

277
00:21:58,920 --> 00:22:01,600
So, you've never been pregnant
or had a miscarriage?

278
00:22:06,440 --> 00:22:07,480
No.

279
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:10,040
I've never been pregnant
or had a miscarriage.

280
00:22:15,760 --> 00:22:17,440
Okay, then.

281
00:22:17,520 --> 00:22:19,640
We'll take a blood test
and check your overall health.

282
00:22:19,720 --> 00:22:21,640
After that, we'll do a pelvic exam.

283
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:24,240
Okay.

284
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:33,280
Take her for the tests,
then bring her back here.

285
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:51,600
This is the house, Pun.

286
00:22:51,680 --> 00:22:54,880
But right now, Mr. Sil's car isn't here.

287
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:56,760
He must be out.

288
00:22:57,280 --> 00:22:58,600
Just wait a moment.

289
00:23:03,040 --> 00:23:04,040
Pun.

290
00:23:04,120 --> 00:23:07,080
Infidelity is something
no one can truly understand.

291
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:10,800
Someone you thought was good
can turn out to be the opposite.

292
00:23:10,880 --> 00:23:12,440
I've been through it myself.

293
00:23:12,520 --> 00:23:16,320
It's best not to trust anyone completely.

294
00:23:41,360 --> 00:23:42,720
Is something wrong?

295
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:47,240
No.

296
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:50,560
- Then please proceed.
- Yes.

297
00:23:52,760 --> 00:23:54,920
Please sit on the bed.

298
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:01,240
Allow me to cover you with a cloth.

299
00:24:01,320 --> 00:24:04,400
Please lift your legs onto the stirrups.

300
00:24:04,920 --> 00:24:06,160
Let me help.

301
00:24:07,080 --> 00:24:08,440
Now the other leg, please.

302
00:24:10,880 --> 00:24:13,760
Okay, slowly lie back.

303
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:17,000
Alright.

304
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:23,160
All done.

305
00:24:26,960 --> 00:24:28,440
You had a miscarriage.

306
00:24:28,520 --> 00:24:31,080
<i>You need to have an emergency curettage.</i>

307
00:24:31,160 --> 00:24:33,520
<i>Mom, I'm sorry. I'm sorry.</i>

308
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:35,200
- <i>I'm so sorry.</i>
- <i>You had a miscarriage.</i>

309
00:24:35,280 --> 00:24:37,960
- <i>I'm sorry, Mom.</i>
- <i>You have to be strong.</i>

310
00:24:43,320 --> 00:24:44,400
Pie.

311
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:46,640
What's wrong?

312
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:49,280
Doctor, I can't do the exam.

313
00:24:49,360 --> 00:24:51,360
- I don't want to do it.
- Pie.

314
00:24:51,440 --> 00:24:52,640
What's going on?

315
00:24:52,720 --> 00:24:54,000
I don't want to do the exam.

316
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:56,520
It's okay to talk about it.

317
00:25:11,080 --> 00:25:13,240
Go out for a moment.
I'll call you when I'm ready.

318
00:25:17,160 --> 00:25:18,640
Do you want to talk to me?

319
00:25:31,680 --> 00:25:33,440
Are you anxious about the pelvic exam?

320
00:25:36,880 --> 00:25:40,800
Should I call Pun to come in for support?

321
00:25:41,440 --> 00:25:42,800
No.

322
00:25:42,880 --> 00:25:44,840
Please don't call him, Doctor.

323
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:01,360
I'm not anxious about the pelvic exam.

324
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:05,520
I'm just afraid you'll find out the truth.

325
00:26:07,880 --> 00:26:10,160
I'm sorry for lying earlier.

326
00:26:11,480 --> 00:26:12,920
The truth is…

327
00:26:19,920 --> 00:26:21,440
I've had a miscarriage.

328
00:26:27,240 --> 00:26:28,960
You are Pun's friend.

329
00:26:30,040 --> 00:26:31,840
So I didn't feel brave enough to tell you.

330
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:34,560
Pun doesn't know about this.

331
00:26:35,800 --> 00:26:38,920
It happened before we started dating.

332
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:42,560
I don't want to disappoint him, Doctor.

333
00:26:46,080 --> 00:26:49,840
Your medical history is confidential.

334
00:26:51,840 --> 00:26:53,320
I won't tell anyone.

335
00:26:55,920 --> 00:27:00,560
Whether they're your husband
or even my friend.

336
00:27:02,640 --> 00:27:04,360
That's the medical code of ethics.

337
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:16,480
Thank you, Doctor.

338
00:27:20,160 --> 00:27:21,200
Pie.

339
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:24,680
Having had a miscarriage

340
00:27:26,280 --> 00:27:28,360
doesn't mean you're a bad person.

341
00:27:36,400 --> 00:27:37,440
Doctor.

342
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:41,360
Is it because I had a miscarriage

343
00:27:42,800 --> 00:27:44,400
that I can't get pregnant again?

344
00:27:47,640 --> 00:27:49,000
It's because of me

345
00:27:49,880 --> 00:27:52,520
that Pun doesn't have children.

346
00:27:53,680 --> 00:27:55,480
Not being able to get pregnant

347
00:27:56,560 --> 00:27:59,760
isn't only caused by a miscarriage.

348
00:28:03,320 --> 00:28:06,960
There are many couples
who are perfectly healthy,

349
00:28:07,040 --> 00:28:10,400
yet still can't get pregnant.

350
00:28:14,600 --> 00:28:16,360
Don't blame yourself, Pie.

351
00:28:20,280 --> 00:28:23,040
Let's focus on finding the real cause.

352
00:28:40,800 --> 00:28:42,040
Thank you, Doctor.

353
00:28:42,560 --> 00:28:43,400
Thank you so much.

354
00:29:07,960 --> 00:29:09,800
Let's go home. This is a waste of time.

355
00:29:11,240 --> 00:29:13,920
You've come this far.
Aren't you going to wait, Pun?

356
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:16,280
I'm not waiting anymore. I'm going back.

357
00:29:16,800 --> 00:29:18,840
I'll just think that maybe
you misunderstood.

358
00:29:22,480 --> 00:29:23,680
Okay, fine.

359
00:29:24,200 --> 00:29:25,280
If you want to go, let's go.

360
00:29:30,400 --> 00:29:32,880
Pun, that's Mr. Sil's car!

361
00:30:10,320 --> 00:30:11,720
I rushed over, afraid you'd get wet.

362
00:30:11,800 --> 00:30:13,800
You're so sweet. Come here.

363
00:30:15,840 --> 00:30:18,560
- I missed you.
- I missed you too.

364
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:30,240
Are you getting out, Pun?

365
00:30:32,560 --> 00:30:34,200
- Go home!
- What?

366
00:30:34,280 --> 00:30:36,640
I said I'm going home. Now!

367
00:30:37,480 --> 00:30:39,680
Okay. If you want to go, let's go.

368
00:31:11,920 --> 00:31:13,520
How is everything, Doctor?

369
00:31:16,560 --> 00:31:18,360
Your uterus looks normal.

370
00:31:18,440 --> 00:31:20,840
And the lining is thick enough.

371
00:31:20,920 --> 00:31:22,760
The fallopian tubes are clear.

372
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:25,080
The reason you're not pregnant

373
00:31:25,160 --> 00:31:27,720
doesn't seem to be related
to your previous miscarriage.

374
00:31:31,120 --> 00:31:34,200
Thank you so much, Doctor.
I really appreciate it.

375
00:31:35,720 --> 00:31:37,600
Don't worry anymore.

376
00:31:37,680 --> 00:31:40,560
Once Pun comes in for the check-up,
we'll talk about having children.

377
00:31:41,880 --> 00:31:42,880
Okay.

378
00:31:48,400 --> 00:31:49,640
Dr. Bee.

379
00:31:51,640 --> 00:31:54,200
Please don't tell him
about my miscarriage yet.

380
00:31:55,320 --> 00:31:57,520
I'll find a chance
to talk to him about it myself.

381
00:32:20,880 --> 00:32:21,720
Pun.

382
00:32:23,040 --> 00:32:25,160
Please don't tell Pie about my dad.

383
00:32:25,240 --> 00:32:26,840
But it already happened.

384
00:32:26,920 --> 00:32:28,360
Don't you think it's better to tell her?

385
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:30,120
You can figure it out together.

386
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:31,640
I can handle it myself.

387
00:32:32,160 --> 00:32:33,960
When I'm ready, I'll tell her.

388
00:33:23,960 --> 00:33:26,280
MOM

389
00:33:36,080 --> 00:33:37,000
Yes, Mom.

390
00:33:37,520 --> 00:33:40,160
I brought Uncle Dech to the museum.

391
00:33:40,240 --> 00:33:41,440
I wanted you to come with us.

392
00:33:41,520 --> 00:33:43,640
Where are you, Pun? Can you come see me?

393
00:33:45,320 --> 00:33:46,200
Sure.

394
00:33:46,720 --> 00:33:47,600
And…

395
00:33:48,760 --> 00:33:50,320
Where are you now?

396
00:33:51,360 --> 00:33:53,760
I'm at the Wang Buttri Museum.

397
00:33:54,360 --> 00:33:56,400
This place is beautiful.
I want my museum like this.

398
00:33:56,920 --> 00:33:58,680
You can do it. You've got it in you.

399
00:33:58,760 --> 00:34:01,200
Hurry and come, okay? Alright.

400
00:34:01,280 --> 00:34:02,800
It's so peaceful here.

401
00:34:23,920 --> 00:34:27,920
WANG BUTTRI MUSEUM

402
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:29,080
Beautiful.

403
00:34:30,639 --> 00:34:33,600
By the way, you have
a lot of valuable things at home.

404
00:34:33,679 --> 00:34:35,400
You could start displaying them now.

405
00:34:35,480 --> 00:34:37,159
Oh, come on.

406
00:34:37,239 --> 00:34:38,440
It's not that much.

407
00:34:38,520 --> 00:34:40,040
I want to keep collecting a little longer.

408
00:34:40,120 --> 00:34:41,480
Oh, madam.

409
00:34:41,560 --> 00:34:43,440
That's enough. If you keep collecting,

410
00:34:43,520 --> 00:34:44,920
you won't have any room to walk.

411
00:34:45,920 --> 00:34:47,080
I'll just expand.

412
00:34:47,159 --> 00:34:48,360
If I need more space, I'll buy more.

413
00:34:48,440 --> 00:34:50,400
Sure, go ahead.

414
00:34:50,480 --> 00:34:52,159
Do whatever you want.

415
00:34:53,560 --> 00:34:55,560
Wow, this table is amazing!

416
00:34:55,639 --> 00:34:57,160
- It's beautiful.
- Yeah.

417
00:34:57,240 --> 00:35:00,040
The wood is really nice.
Oh, look over there!

418
00:35:41,640 --> 00:35:43,280
How long have you been standing here?

419
00:35:44,280 --> 00:35:47,960
Since you seemed
like you were about to tear up.

420
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:55,040
I don't know what you're thinking.

421
00:35:56,880 --> 00:35:59,040
But it reminded me
of when I was in England.

422
00:36:02,560 --> 00:36:05,480
There were many times I felt lost,

423
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:07,800
like no one was there for me.

424
00:36:09,640 --> 00:36:12,520
I didn't know who to talk to.

425
00:36:13,400 --> 00:36:14,640
And I wasn't sure

426
00:36:15,240 --> 00:36:18,080
if anyone would even understand me.

427
00:36:21,960 --> 00:36:24,480
But if you need to talk to someone,

428
00:36:25,720 --> 00:36:28,360
I'm the one you can trust.

429
00:36:32,920 --> 00:36:34,560
I'll go ahead and clear the way for you.

430
00:36:34,640 --> 00:36:36,160
When you're ready, follow me.

431
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:21,400
I'm sorry, Mr. Sil.

432
00:37:21,480 --> 00:37:23,760
I really had to do this for Pie.

433
00:37:33,960 --> 00:37:35,040
Mom.

434
00:37:36,040 --> 00:37:36,960
Pie!

435
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:40,600
How was the doctor's visit?

436
00:37:40,680 --> 00:37:42,880
What did the doctor say?
Did she ask about that?

437
00:37:44,920 --> 00:37:46,880
Everything's fine, no issues.

438
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:50,680
That's a relief.

439
00:37:50,760 --> 00:37:51,760
But…

440
00:37:52,880 --> 00:37:54,960
for the next appointment,
Pun needs to come too.

441
00:37:55,520 --> 00:37:56,680
Really?

442
00:38:02,360 --> 00:38:03,240
Mom.

443
00:38:06,360 --> 00:38:09,320
When you were with Dad,

444
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:12,480
did you ever feel like…

445
00:38:14,880 --> 00:38:16,720
there was some kind of distance?

446
00:38:17,520 --> 00:38:21,200
Like there was an invisible wall
between you and Dad?

447
00:38:21,760 --> 00:38:23,520
Did you ever feel like that?

448
00:38:24,200 --> 00:38:25,040
Hey.

449
00:38:25,560 --> 00:38:27,680
Don't ask about me.

450
00:38:28,560 --> 00:38:31,040
Are you feeling like that now?

451
00:38:36,720 --> 00:38:42,600
I think you need to get past it
and focus on having a baby.

452
00:38:42,680 --> 00:38:44,920
Everything will get better after that.

453
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:47,400
Mom, I totally see it differently.

454
00:38:48,920 --> 00:38:52,000
If there are still problems between us,
we shouldn't have a child.

455
00:38:52,080 --> 00:38:54,400
If we have one and things get worse,
leading to separation,

456
00:38:54,480 --> 00:38:55,640
it would be bad for the child.

457
00:38:55,720 --> 00:38:56,920
Hey, Pie.

458
00:38:57,000 --> 00:39:00,280
Stop! Don't talk about divorce,
and don't even think about it.

459
00:39:00,360 --> 00:39:04,680
Whatever wall is in the way,
you need to break it down.

460
00:39:05,760 --> 00:39:07,200
Pie.

461
00:39:07,880 --> 00:39:10,080
Don't overthink things.

462
00:39:10,160 --> 00:39:13,520
Men can have their secrets.
It's not a big deal.

463
00:39:13,600 --> 00:39:17,080
If they don't want you to know,
you don't need to.

464
00:39:17,160 --> 00:39:18,800
And if one day he's ready to tell you,

465
00:39:18,880 --> 00:39:20,640
he'll tell you when the time comes.

466
00:39:21,160 --> 00:39:24,440
Just be a good wife, Pie.

467
00:39:25,040 --> 00:39:27,920
Stand by Pun, and be his support.

468
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:29,880
And don't create problems.

469
00:39:30,640 --> 00:39:34,120
Pun is the best man.

470
00:39:54,640 --> 00:39:56,000
Hello!

471
00:39:56,080 --> 00:39:58,320
I passed by the noodle shop
and got some for you.

472
00:40:00,800 --> 00:40:02,520
Pun wants to go over work as well.

473
00:40:02,600 --> 00:40:04,200
Let's talk while eating, okay?

474
00:40:13,720 --> 00:40:15,360
Your house is very stylish.

475
00:40:15,440 --> 00:40:17,400
It's my senior's house.
I rent it from him.

476
00:40:20,840 --> 00:40:22,000
- Have a bowl.
- Let me do it.

477
00:40:22,600 --> 00:40:24,200
You bought the food, so just wait.

478
00:40:25,400 --> 00:40:26,440
Okay.

479
00:40:34,080 --> 00:40:35,800
You dress like this on your day off?

480
00:40:35,880 --> 00:40:37,320
It's totally different from the office.

481
00:40:41,520 --> 00:40:43,960
You noticed I changed my style?

482
00:40:44,600 --> 00:40:46,040
Well, it's obvious.

483
00:40:46,120 --> 00:40:49,160
If you don't notice,
it should still be clear.

484
00:40:50,640 --> 00:40:51,840
Do you like it?

485
00:40:53,720 --> 00:40:54,600
Well…

486
00:40:55,680 --> 00:40:58,280
It's up to the person wearing it.
What they like is best.

487
00:40:59,680 --> 00:41:01,720
Such an open-minded gentleman.

488
00:41:01,800 --> 00:41:03,200
You're overdoing it.

489
00:41:04,280 --> 00:41:05,560
Here, done.

490
00:41:05,640 --> 00:41:07,000
Thank you.

491
00:41:08,080 --> 00:41:10,000
- Does it look good?
- It looks fine.

492
00:41:10,600 --> 00:41:13,000
- Want some coffee? I'll make it.
- Yes.

493
00:41:13,600 --> 00:41:15,320
- Just wait a minute.
- Okay.

494
00:41:34,560 --> 00:41:35,640
Looks so good.

495
00:41:36,160 --> 00:41:37,480
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

496
00:41:37,560 --> 00:41:38,840
- That's so sweet.
- Serve me too.

497
00:41:40,800 --> 00:41:42,320
Pun, you should eat too.

498
00:41:49,080 --> 00:41:52,040
We don't often eat together.
Let's get a photo.

499
00:41:52,680 --> 00:41:55,160
Sure, dear. That's a good idea.

500
00:41:56,120 --> 00:41:58,240
Excuse me. Can you take a photo for us?

501
00:42:02,440 --> 00:42:03,320
Come on.

502
00:42:05,880 --> 00:42:07,080
Give us a smile.

503
00:42:48,280 --> 00:42:49,400
Win, look at this.

504
00:42:49,480 --> 00:42:52,400
She's posting like she's Pun's wife.
Isn't that too much?

505
00:42:54,040 --> 00:42:55,440
Better send it to Pie.

506
00:42:55,520 --> 00:42:57,600
Let her show who the real wife is.

507
00:42:57,680 --> 00:42:58,920
Maybe she'll get mad at Pun for once.

508
00:42:59,880 --> 00:43:00,920
Just screenshot it.

509
00:43:01,640 --> 00:43:04,000
- Does she usually get angry?
- Not at all.

510
00:43:04,080 --> 00:43:05,600
She won't react,
no matter how much you push.

511
00:43:05,680 --> 00:43:08,440
She never gets mad or jealous.

512
00:43:10,640 --> 00:43:12,560
Not getting mad
doesn't mean she doesn't care.

513
00:43:13,400 --> 00:43:15,360
Sending the picture will just worry her.

514
00:43:19,960 --> 00:43:21,000
Don't send it.

515
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:27,240
You're right.

516
00:43:28,800 --> 00:43:30,080
I won't send it.

517
00:43:32,080 --> 00:43:33,160
Good.

518
00:43:33,240 --> 00:43:34,600
It's between the two of them.

519
00:43:34,680 --> 00:43:36,280
Let them handle it.

520
00:43:36,360 --> 00:43:37,680
I'm not sure they'll handle it.

521
00:43:37,760 --> 00:43:40,720
Whenever something's wrong,
Pie always keeps it to herself.

522
00:43:40,800 --> 00:43:43,280
Even if she's overthinking,
she'll say she's not.

523
00:43:44,640 --> 00:43:46,840
Someone like her
never shares her struggles.

524
00:43:46,920 --> 00:43:49,160
If something's wrong,
she won't tell anyone.

525
00:43:49,240 --> 00:43:52,960
She has to reach her breaking point
before she explodes.

526
00:43:55,160 --> 00:43:57,880
I don't want her
to keep it all inside like this.

527
00:43:58,400 --> 00:44:01,880
I'm afraid one day she'll explode at Pun,

528
00:44:01,960 --> 00:44:03,360
and everything will fall apart.

529
00:44:25,440 --> 00:44:27,480
- Where's Dad?
- He went to a meditation retreat.

530
00:44:50,160 --> 00:44:51,440
Do you feel better?

531
00:44:57,640 --> 00:45:00,120
Well, I'm feeling a bit better.

532
00:45:02,880 --> 00:45:06,280
If you're feeling better,
then I'm relieved.

533
00:45:09,680 --> 00:45:10,520
Mink.

534
00:45:15,600 --> 00:45:17,080
Don't you want to know…

535
00:45:19,120 --> 00:45:20,720
what problems I'm facing,

536
00:45:21,240 --> 00:45:22,560
or what I'm thinking?

537
00:45:24,400 --> 00:45:25,760
I do want to know.

538
00:45:26,760 --> 00:45:30,040
But if you're not sharing,
it means you don't want to talk about it.

539
00:45:31,240 --> 00:45:32,720
So I won't ask.

540
00:45:33,400 --> 00:45:35,320
If you want to talk, you'll tell me.

541
00:45:40,440 --> 00:45:43,520
Thanks a lot for understanding me.

542
00:45:46,840 --> 00:45:50,160
For you, Pun, I'm always happy to help.

543
00:46:26,320 --> 00:46:28,200
Pun!

544
00:46:31,160 --> 00:46:34,040
Dr. Bee asked when you're going
for the check-up.

545
00:46:35,440 --> 00:46:36,880
I'll call her myself.

546
00:46:37,600 --> 00:46:39,800
I want to take care of some things first.

547
00:46:40,520 --> 00:46:41,600
Pun.

548
00:46:49,680 --> 00:46:51,600
I need to talk to you about something.

549
00:46:54,440 --> 00:46:56,680
Is it urgent, Pie?
If not, let's wait a bit.

550
00:46:57,600 --> 00:46:59,400
I have a lot to think about right now.

551
00:47:00,640 --> 00:47:02,800
Once I handle everything,
I'll listen to you.

552
00:47:06,480 --> 00:47:07,520
Okay.

553
00:47:08,440 --> 00:47:09,720
I'll handle work first.

554
00:49:45,040 --> 00:49:47,400
Pie, you're here so early.

555
00:49:47,480 --> 00:49:48,960
Hello, Uncle Dech.

556
00:49:49,040 --> 00:49:51,600
I woke up early, so I came early.

557
00:49:52,200 --> 00:49:53,720
What are you working on?

558
00:49:54,280 --> 00:49:58,600
I've nearly finished gathering the fabrics
to showcase, as you suggested.

559
00:49:59,240 --> 00:50:01,560
But the issue is that some of the pieces

560
00:50:01,640 --> 00:50:03,720
still don't have
complete historical information.

561
00:50:03,800 --> 00:50:06,440
So, I'm collecting photos
and consulting other professors.

562
00:50:06,520 --> 00:50:08,600
Mink mentioned it to me too.

563
00:50:08,680 --> 00:50:10,400
But I really can't help with that.

564
00:50:10,480 --> 00:50:13,800
Because the fabrics I have
are from before I was even born.

565
00:50:17,240 --> 00:50:18,240
Oh, wait!

566
00:50:18,320 --> 00:50:19,960
But there is someone who knows.

567
00:50:20,040 --> 00:50:20,880
Who is it?

568
00:50:20,960 --> 00:50:22,360
Aunt Khamman.

569
00:50:22,440 --> 00:50:24,360
She's probably
from your grandmother's generation.

570
00:50:24,440 --> 00:50:26,320
She used to be my mom's assistant.

571
00:50:26,400 --> 00:50:29,960
She managed the family's treasures
and shopped for fabrics with my mom.

572
00:50:30,040 --> 00:50:31,920
She knows a lot and is very knowledgeable.

573
00:50:32,000 --> 00:50:34,400
But she's not here anymore.

574
00:50:34,480 --> 00:50:37,080
She moved back to Mae Hong Son.

575
00:50:37,160 --> 00:50:39,320
I can definitely go
to Mae Hong Son, Uncle Dech.

576
00:50:39,400 --> 00:50:41,000
I'll go anywhere
as long as the work gets done.

577
00:50:42,400 --> 00:50:43,920
I really picked the right person.

578
00:50:44,000 --> 00:50:47,720
I'll send you her address,
and you can contact her.

579
00:50:47,800 --> 00:50:50,040
- Sure. Thank you so much.
- You're welcome.

580
00:50:53,280 --> 00:50:55,880
By the way, are you here alone today?

581
00:50:55,960 --> 00:50:57,160
Where's Pun?

582
00:50:58,800 --> 00:51:00,680
Yes, I came by myself.

583
00:51:02,960 --> 00:51:05,120
I'm going to take photos
and gather information.

584
00:51:05,200 --> 00:51:07,280
- Alright, take your time.
- Thank you.

585
00:51:16,960 --> 00:51:18,360
You're not overthinking, right?

586
00:51:23,760 --> 00:51:24,880
Me?

587
00:51:25,960 --> 00:51:27,160
Overthinking what?

588
00:51:28,960 --> 00:51:34,120
About how I, Pun, and Aunt Nhun,
get along so well.

589
00:51:34,960 --> 00:51:36,360
You're not overthinking it, are you?

590
00:51:40,600 --> 00:51:42,760
- No.
- Are you pretending?

591
00:51:43,280 --> 00:51:45,080
If you are overthinking, just say so.

592
00:51:45,160 --> 00:51:47,680
This kind of thing is obvious.

593
00:51:47,760 --> 00:51:49,400
If it's obvious, then don't ask.

594
00:51:49,480 --> 00:51:50,440
It's illogical.

595
00:51:51,960 --> 00:51:53,200
Wait.

596
00:51:56,120 --> 00:51:58,800
I'm asking because I feel sorry for you.

597
00:51:59,720 --> 00:52:03,120
But if you don't mind, aren't bothered,

598
00:52:04,000 --> 00:52:07,200
not comparing yourself
and feeling inferior,

599
00:52:08,240 --> 00:52:11,920
and not thinking negatively
about me trying to take the spotlight,

600
00:52:12,720 --> 00:52:14,200
then I'm relieved.

601
00:52:17,760 --> 00:52:20,840
Honestly, I admire you.

602
00:52:25,720 --> 00:52:28,720
A smart person like you should see

603
00:52:28,800 --> 00:52:31,040
that you don't fit in with Pun's family,

604
00:52:31,120 --> 00:52:32,240
but you're pushing through.

605
00:52:33,960 --> 00:52:36,320
How do you do it? You're impressive.

606
00:52:37,080 --> 00:52:39,480
If it were me,
I would have given up long ago.

607
00:52:41,360 --> 00:52:44,640
Seriously, are you happy
with how things are now?

608
00:52:48,840 --> 00:52:50,360
And are you happy?

609
00:52:50,920 --> 00:52:52,720
Saying things like this to someone's face.

610
00:52:55,680 --> 00:52:58,440
If you can be happy
at the expense of someone else's pain,

611
00:52:58,960 --> 00:53:00,520
then I have to admire you.

612
00:53:00,600 --> 00:53:02,040
You're really something.

613
00:53:02,560 --> 00:53:03,840
If it were me,

614
00:53:05,160 --> 00:53:07,560
I wouldn't dare say
something like this to someone's face.

615
00:53:08,760 --> 00:53:10,160
My heart couldn't take it.

616
00:53:11,440 --> 00:53:12,480
I just couldn't do it.

617
00:53:30,160 --> 00:53:31,000
What's up, Rok?

618
00:53:31,080 --> 00:53:32,680
Did you get in touch with Pun?

619
00:53:32,760 --> 00:53:34,880
I've been calling all morning,
but can't reach him.

620
00:53:34,960 --> 00:53:36,200
There are documents for his signature.

621
00:53:36,800 --> 00:53:39,160
I can't reach him either.
I've called multiple times.

622
00:53:39,800 --> 00:53:42,200
I'm heading to the office now. See you.

623
00:53:50,640 --> 00:53:52,800
PUN

624
00:54:03,720 --> 00:54:04,720
Pie!

625
00:54:05,280 --> 00:54:06,760
Have you reached Pun yet?

626
00:54:09,720 --> 00:54:12,640
This is strange.
He never disappears like this.

627
00:54:41,760 --> 00:54:42,800
Hey!

628
00:54:42,880 --> 00:54:45,280
- What? Really?
- Pun just texted me!

629
00:54:45,360 --> 00:54:48,040
He said to cancel today's client meeting.
He's not coming in.

630
00:54:48,920 --> 00:54:51,200
But he didn't say
where he's going or what he's doing.

631
00:54:51,280 --> 00:54:52,760
Has he contacted you yet?

632
00:54:53,520 --> 00:54:55,600
No. You know more than I do.

633
00:54:57,240 --> 00:54:58,200
Hey.

634
00:54:58,280 --> 00:55:00,080
I'm his assistant, so he has to tell me.

635
00:55:00,160 --> 00:55:02,080
Otherwise, the clients will be mad.

636
00:55:02,160 --> 00:55:03,840
He's probably off working on new deals.

637
00:55:03,920 --> 00:55:05,320
Don't overthink it.

638
00:55:12,440 --> 00:55:13,680
- Hey, Rok.
- Yes?

639
00:55:13,760 --> 00:55:16,840
I talked to Uncle Dech this morning.

640
00:55:16,920 --> 00:55:20,040
About going to gather information
on the fabrics from an elderly person

641
00:55:20,120 --> 00:55:21,320
who knows about his family's fabrics.

642
00:55:22,320 --> 00:55:23,800
I got her contact number.

643
00:55:23,880 --> 00:55:26,880
So, I'm thinking of going
to Mae Hong Son tomorrow.

644
00:55:27,680 --> 00:55:29,480
Are you doing anything?
Wanna come with me?

645
00:55:30,040 --> 00:55:31,120
Sure!

646
00:55:31,200 --> 00:55:33,520
I'm bored anyway,
and I feel like traveling.

647
00:55:34,760 --> 00:55:36,040
I'll invite Win to come along.

648
00:55:36,560 --> 00:55:39,280
Hey, don't mix work with personal stuff.

649
00:55:39,360 --> 00:55:41,080
Hey, Pie!

650
00:55:41,160 --> 00:55:43,600
Doesn't it involve him too?

651
00:55:43,680 --> 00:55:44,920
I'm good not going.

652
00:55:46,320 --> 00:55:47,680
You should just go together.

653
00:55:48,280 --> 00:55:50,520
If I have something urgent, I'll go later.

654
00:56:04,880 --> 00:56:08,080
Hello. This is Khun Pun's office.

655
00:56:31,280 --> 00:56:33,160
Grow well, my plant.

656
00:56:45,560 --> 00:56:47,320
Hey, what's going on?

657
00:56:51,640 --> 00:56:52,640
Pun?

658
00:56:54,880 --> 00:56:55,960
How did you get here?

659
00:56:56,480 --> 00:56:57,480
And…

660
00:56:58,360 --> 00:56:59,600
How long have you been here?

661
00:57:02,080 --> 00:57:03,800
Afraid your wife and kid will see me?

662
00:57:11,400 --> 00:57:13,080
How can you stay calm about this?

663
00:57:13,600 --> 00:57:15,520
It's like this isn't a big deal.

664
00:57:19,360 --> 00:57:20,240
Pun.

665
00:57:21,800 --> 00:57:22,960
You're grown up now.

666
00:57:23,680 --> 00:57:25,120
You should understand.

667
00:57:25,720 --> 00:57:27,280
Understand what, Dad?

668
00:57:27,360 --> 00:57:30,400
Understand you've been lying to us,
and that you have another family?

669
00:57:31,160 --> 00:57:32,800
Or now that I'm grown up,

670
00:57:32,880 --> 00:57:35,080
I should just accept everything you do,
even if it's wrong?

671
00:57:35,160 --> 00:57:37,400
Let me be clear. I don't understand.

672
00:57:38,640 --> 00:57:40,840
I don't know how long
you've been lying to us.

673
00:57:41,440 --> 00:57:42,600
But you have to make a choice.

674
00:57:42,680 --> 00:57:44,000
Today, you have to end this.

675
00:57:47,280 --> 00:57:49,960
In a marriage,
there's a limit to patience.

676
00:57:50,040 --> 00:57:51,360
By cheating?

677
00:57:51,440 --> 00:57:54,920
By finding someone who values us more!

678
00:57:55,000 --> 00:57:58,480
Have you ever thought
about what you'd do if Dad cheated?

679
00:57:58,560 --> 00:58:00,560
Where would he find
a woman better than me?

680
00:58:00,640 --> 00:58:01,600
There's no one.

681
00:58:01,680 --> 00:58:04,760
Okay! You never did anything wrong.
You're always right.

682
00:58:07,400 --> 00:58:09,120
Don't talk to me like that!

683
00:58:09,200 --> 00:58:10,760
Let's not be together anymore.

684
00:58:10,840 --> 00:58:11,920
- Pie, where are you going?
- Pun. Pun!

685
00:58:12,000 --> 00:58:13,080
- I won't let you leave!
- Pun!

686
00:58:13,160 --> 00:58:15,360
- Pun, don't!
- Pie, come back!

687
00:58:15,440 --> 00:58:16,880
Please take care of her for me.

688
00:58:19,480 --> 00:58:20,960
We can still be friends.

689
00:58:21,560 --> 00:58:22,600
Trust me.

690
00:58:51,880 --> 00:58:54,320
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
